            title="Safety Stickers and Adhesive Decals"
            imagePosition="right"
        >
            <p class="mb-4">We print peel and stick safety stickers and adhesive decals for walls, counters, doors, equipment, and any smooth surface in your facility. Unlike rigid safety signs, adhesive decals can go places a sign cannot. They conform to curved surfaces, stick to equipment, fit inside tight spaces, and apply to glass, metal, plastic, and painted drywall without any hardware or mounting. For businesses in Joliet and Will County that need to communicate safety guidelines across many different surfaces and locations, adhesive decals are the most flexible and affordable solution available.</p>
            <p class="mb-4">We print safety stickers on durable outdoor rated vinyl that resists moisture, cleaning chemicals, and UV exposure. This means your safety stickers hold up whether they are placed on a restroom door, a refrigerator handle, a window frame, or an outdoor surface near your entrance. The ink we use is fade resistant so the safety message stays legible for as long as the sticker is in place. We also offer removable adhesive versions for customers who need to rotate stickers in and out as policies change without leaving any marks on the surface.</p>
            <p>We print safety stickers in English and Spanish and can include icons and graphics that make the message clear regardless of language. We have worked with restaurants, medical offices, retail stores, schools, and manufacturing facilities in Joliet, Shorewood, Crest Hill, Plainfield, and throughout the greater Chicagoland area. Reach out to us at (815) 349 8600 and let us help you create the right sticker package for your facility.</p>
        </x-sections.card-image-with-text>

        <x-sections.card-image-with-text
            image="/images/corona-virus-signs/top5pct-covid19-signs-stickers-joliet-shorewood.jpg"
