            <p class="mb-4">We print COVID compliance decals and health protocol stickers for businesses that need to communicate capacity limits, sanitation requirements, and visitor guidelines in a clear and professional way. These adhesive decals are designed to go directly on surfaces where customers and employees interact most, such as checkout counters, elevator buttons, door handles, hand sanitizer stations, and any other high touch point in your facility. Putting the safety message exactly where people are already looking makes the guidance more effective and easier to follow.</p>
            <p class="mb-4">Our compliance decals are different from compliance signs in one important way: they adhere directly to the surface rather than hanging or standing near it. A floor sticker placed six feet behind the person at the checkout counter tells the next customer exactly where to stand without any confusion. A counter sticker on the credit card reader tells customers which side of the plexiglass barrier to face. A door sticker at eye level reminds people to use hand sanitizer before entering. These small placement decisions make a big difference in how smoothly your space operates during busy periods.</p>
            <p>We help businesses across Joliet, Shorewood, Romeoville, Lockport, and all of Will County create cohesive compliance decal packages that cover every surface and every interaction point in their facility. Whether you need three decals for a small office or three hundred for a large retail or healthcare environment, we have the capacity to deliver quickly and affordably. Call us at (815) 349 8600 or visit us at 121 Springfield Avenue in Joliet to get your order started today.</p>
